{"timestamp":1774427597559,"source_app":"agentic-harness","session_id":"e1a06592-fa9e-404a-b4ed-8f1872c70050","hook_event_type":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q2j44ryLbkY4n4NewLf9Uh","payload":{"session_id":"e1a06592-fa9e-404a-b4ed-8f1872c70050","transcript_path":"/Users/auto/.claude/projects/-Users-auto-agentic-harness-apps-mas-trees-bdf67753/e1a06592-fa9e-404a-b4ed-8f1872c70050.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/bdf67753","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/bdf67753/specs/patch/patch-commit-hydrate-test-changes.md","content":"# Patch: Commit uncommitted unit tests for free-trial CTA filtering\n\n## Metadata\nadw_id: ``\nreview_change_request: `Issue #1: The four new unit tests in web-components/test/hydrate.test.js are unstaged/uncommitted and will not be included in CI without a commit. Resolution: Stage and commit web-components/test/hydrate.test.js alongside the hydrate.js feature commit. Severity: tech_debt`\n\n## Issue Summary\n**Original Spec:** specs/issue-bdf67753-adw-1d78f7d6-sdlc_planner-hide-free-trial-ctas-plan-pages.md\n**Issue:** Four new unit tests covering the free-trial CTA filtering logic were written in `web-components/test/hydrate.test.js` but left unstaged/uncommitted. They exist only as a working-tree modification and will not be picked up by CI.\n**Solution:** Stage `web-components/test/hydrate.test.js` and commit it so the tests are part of the feature branch history and included in CI runs.\n\n## Files to Modify\nUse these files to implement the patch:\n\n- `web-components/test/hydrate.test.js` \u2014 already contains the four new test cases; just needs to be staged and committed (no code edits required)\n\n## Implementation Steps\nIMPORTANT: Execute every step in order, top to bottom.\n\n### Step 1: Verify the diff contains only the expected test additions\n- Run `git diff web-components/test/hydrate.test.js` and confirm the only changes are the four new `it()` blocks inside the `processCTAs` describe block.\n\n### Step 2: Stage the test file\n- Run `git add web-components/test/hydrate.test.js`\n\n### Step 3: Commit the staged file\n- Run `git commit -m \"test(hydrate): add unit tests for free-trial CTA filtering on plans variants\"`\n\n## Validation\nExecute every command to validate the patch is complete with zero regressions.\n\n```bash\n# Confirm test file is now committed (no unstaged changes)\ngit status web-components/test/hydrate.test.js\n\n# Confirm the four new tests appear in the latest commit\ngit show --stat HEAD\n\n# Syntax-check the test file\nnode --check web-components/test/hydrate.test.js\n```\n\n## Patch Scope\n**Lines of code to change:** 0 (file already edited; only a git stage + commit is needed)\n**Risk level:** low\n**Testing required:** Confirm `git status` shows no unstaged changes for the test file; confirm `git show HEAD` includes the test file.\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q2j44ryLbkY4n4NewLf9Uh"}}
